Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Pour 300ml cold salted @water{300%ml} into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Add the @rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover, and cook for ~{10%mins}.

Remove from the heat. Stir through half the @green pesto{30%g} then pop the lid back on the #pot{}.

Keep covered for ~{10%mins} or until ready to serve.

> TIP: If you prefer, use the pesto as a garnish instead.

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, combine the @breadcrumbs{1%pack} with the @Irish pork mince{240%g}, @dried oregano{1%sachet} and half the @grated Italian style hard cheese{2%units}.

Add 2 tbsp @water{2%tbsp} and @salt{1/4%tsp}. Season with @pepper{to taste} and mix together by hand.

Roll into evenly-sized balls, 3-4 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the meatballs onto a lined #baking tray{}.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2%units}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Place a #pan{} over medium-high heat.

Add the onion and garlic and fry for ~{2-3%mins}.

Stir in @passata{1%pack}, 100ml @water{100%ml} and @sugar{1/2%tsp}.

Add the cooked meatballs and half the @creme fraiche{110%g} and allow to warm through. Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @sugar{to taste}.

Mix the remaining pesto and creme fraiche together.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if the sauce is too thick.

Fluff up the pesto rice with a #fork{} and divide between #bowls{}.

Top with the meatballs and sauce.

Finish with a drizzle of pesto creme fraiche and a sprinkling of cheese.